        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 28 at 5:52PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 552 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Mansfield, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coushatta, Edgefield, Armistead, Evelyn, Hanna, Rambin, Lake End,
Ajax and Grand Bayou.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
